fields.title: Activity Selection (Greedy)
fields.description:
Activity Selection

Given n activities with start and finish times, find the maximum number of activities that can be performed by a single person (a person can only work on one activity at a time).

Example

Input:
4
1 3
2 5
4 7
1 8
Output: 2
fields.input_format:
First line: n
Next n lines: start finish
fields.output_format: Maximum number of non-overlapping activities

fields.title: Merge Sorted Arrays
fields.description:
Merge Sorted Arrays

Given two sorted integer arrays nums1 and nums2, merge them into a single sorted array and print it.

Example

Input:
3
1 3 5
3
2 4 6
Output: 1 2 3 4 5 6
fields.input_format:
First line: n
Second line: n sorted integers
Third line: m
Fourth line: m sorted integers
fields.output_format: Space-separated merged sorted array

fields.title: Count Vowels
fields.description: Given a string S, count the number of vowels (a, e, i, o, u ΓÇö both uppercase and lowercase).
fields.input_format: A single line containing a string S.
fields.output_format: Print the number of vowels in S.

fields.title: 0/1 Knapsack
fields.description:
You are given N items, each with a weight and a value. You have a knapsack that can carry a maximum weight of W.

Determine the maximum total value you can carry. You may include each item at most once.
fields.input_format:
First line: N W
Next N lines: weight_i value_i
fields.output_format: Print the maximum total value.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ N Γëñ 1000
1 Γëñ W Γëñ 1000
1 Γëñ weight_i, value_i Γëñ 1000

fields.title: Palindrome Check
fields.description:
Given a string S (lowercase letters only), determine whether it is a palindrome.

A palindrome reads the same forward and backward.
fields.input_format: A single line containing a string S (lowercase letters only, no spaces).
fields.output_format: Print "YES" if S is a palindrome, otherwise print "NO".

fields.title: Sum of Digits
fields.description:
Given a non-negative integer N, find the sum of all its digits.

Example: For N = 1234, the sum is 1+2+3+4 = 10.
fields.input_format: A single line containing a non-negative integer N.
fields.output_format: Print the sum of digits of N.

fields.title: Two Sum
fields.description: Given two integers a and b, print their sum.
fields.input_format: Two integers a and b separated by a space.
fields.output_format: A single integer, the sum of a and b.

fields.title: Second Largest Element
fields.description: Given an array of N distinct integers, find the second largest element.
fields.input_format:
First line: N (size of array).
Second line: N space-separated integers.
fields.output_format: Print the second largest element.
fields.constraints:
2 Γëñ N Γëñ 10^5
-10^9 Γëñ A[i] Γëñ 10^9
All elements are distinct.

fields.title: Sort an Array
fields.description: Given an array of N integers, sort them in non-decreasing order and print the result.
fields.input_format:
First line: N.
Second line: N space-separated integers.
fields.output_format: Print the sorted array on a single line with elements separated by spaces.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ N Γëñ 10^5
-10^9 Γëñ A[i] Γëñ 10^9

fields.title: FizzBuzz
fields.description:
FizzBuzz

Given an integer n, print numbers from 1 to n. For multiples of 3, print Fizz; for multiples of 5, print Buzz; for multiples of both, print FizzBuzz.

Example

Input: 5
Output:
1
2
Fizz
4
Buzz
fields.input_format: A single integer n
fields.output_format: n lines of output

fields.title: Longest Common Subsequence
fields.description:
Given two strings A and B, find the length of their Longest Common Subsequence (LCS).

A subsequence is a sequence derived from another by deleting some or no characters without changing the order of the remaining characters.

Example: LCS of ABCBDAB and BDCAB is BCAB with length 4.
fields.input_format: Two lines, each containing a string.
fields.output_format: Print the length of the LCS.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ |A|, |B| Γëñ 1000
Strings contain only uppercase English letters.

fields.title: Fibonacci Number
fields.description:
Given an integer N, print the N-th Fibonacci number.

The Fibonacci sequence is defined as:

  • F(0) = 0
  • F(1) = 1
  • F(N) = F(N-1) + F(N-2) for N ΓëÑ 2
fields.input_format: A single integer N.
fields.output_format: Print the N-th Fibonacci number.

fields.title: Topological Sort
fields.description:
Topological Sort

Given a directed acyclic graph (DAG) with n nodes and m edges, output a valid topological ordering. If multiple orderings exist, output the lexicographically smallest one.

Example

Input:
4 4
3 0
3 1
0 1
0 2
Output: 3 0 1 2
fields.input_format:
First line: n m
Next m lines: u v (directed edge u -> v)
fields.output_format: Space-separated topological order

fields.title: Detect Cycle in Graph
fields.description:
Detect Cycle in Graph

Given a directed graph with n nodes and m edges, determine if the graph contains a cycle.

Example

Input:
3 3
0 1
1 2
2 0
Output: true
fields.input_format:
First line: n m
Next m lines: u v (directed edge from u to v)
fields.output_format: true or false

fields.title: Graph BFS Shortest Path
fields.description:
Graph BFS Shortest Path

Given an unweighted undirected graph with n nodes (0-indexed) and m edges, find the shortest path length from node 0 to node n-1. If no path exists, return -1.

Example

Input:
4 4
0 1
1 2
2 3
0 3
Output: 1
fields.input_format:
First line: n m (nodes, edges)
Next m lines: u v (edge between u and v)
fields.output_format: Shortest path length from 0 to n-1, or -1

fields.title: Reverse a String
fields.description: Given a string S, print the string in reverse order.
fields.input_format: A single line containing a string S.
fields.output_format: Print the reversed string on a single line.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ |S| Γëñ 10^5
S contains only printable ASCII characters.

fields.title: Anagram Check
fields.description:
Given two strings A and B, determine if they are anagrams of each other.

Two strings are anagrams if one can be formed by rearranging the letters of the other (ignoring case).
fields.input_format: Two lines, each containing a string (one word, no spaces).
fields.output_format: Print "YES" if the strings are anagrams, else "NO".
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ |A|, |B| Γëñ 10^5
Strings contain only alphabetic characters.

fields.title: Edit Distance
fields.description:
Given two strings A and B, find the minimum number of operations required to convert A into B.

Allowed operations:

  • Insert a character
  • Delete a character
  • Replace a character

This is also known as the Levenshtein Distance.
fields.input_format: Two lines, each containing a string.
fields.output_format: Print the minimum edit distance.
fields.constraints:
0 Γëñ |A|, |B| Γëñ 1000
Strings contain only lowercase English letters.

fields.title: Prime Number Check
fields.description:
Given T test cases, for each integer N, determine if it is prime.

A prime number is greater than 1 and has no divisors other than 1 and itself.
fields.input_format:
First line: T (number of test cases).
Next T lines: one integer N each.
fields.output_format: For each N, print "PRIME" if it is prime, else "NOT PRIME".
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ T Γëñ 100
1 Γëñ N Γëñ 10^9

fields.title: Reverse String
fields.description:
Reverse String

Write a function that reverses a string. The input string is given as a single line.

Example

Input: hello
Output: olleh
fields.input_format: A single string s
fields.output_format: The reversed string
fields.constraints:
1 <= len(s) <= 10^5
s contains only printable ASCII characters

fields.title: Binary to Decimal
fields.description: Given a binary string (consisting only of '0' and '1'), convert it to its decimal equivalent.
fields.input_format: A single line containing a binary string B.
fields.output_format: Print the decimal value of B.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ |B| Γëñ 63
B contains only '0' and '1'.
The result fits in a 64-bit signed integer.

fields.title: Maximum Subarray Sum
fields.description:
Given an array of N integers (which may include negative numbers), find the maximum sum of a contiguous subarray.

This is the classic Kadane's Algorithm problem.

Note: The subarray must contain at least one element.
fields.input_format:
First line: N.
Second line: N space-separated integers.
fields.output_format: Print the maximum subarray sum.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ N Γëñ 10^5
-10^4 Γëñ A[i] Γëñ 10^4

fields.title: Coin Change Problem
fields.description:
Coin Change

Given an array of coin denominations and a target amount, return the fewest number of coins needed to make up that amount. If it's not possible, return -1.

Example

Input:
3
1 2 5
11
Output: 3

Explanation: 11 = 5 + 5 + 1
fields.input_format:
First line: n (number of coin types)
Second line: n coin denominations
Third line: target amount
fields.output_format: Minimum coins needed, or -1

fields.title: Invert Binary Tree
fields.description:
Invert Binary Tree

Given a binary tree as array input (level order, -1 for null), invert it and print the level order traversal of the inverted tree.

Example

Input: 7
4 2 7 1 3 6 9
Output: 4 7 2 9 6 3 1
fields.input_format:
First line: n
Second line: n integers (-1 = null)
fields.output_format: Space-separated level order of inverted tree (exclude nulls at end)

fields.title: Level Order Traversal
fields.description:
Level Order Traversal

Given a binary tree as an array (level order with -1 for null nodes), print the level order traversal with each level on a new line.

Example

Input: 7
3 9 20 -1 -1 15 7
Output:
3
9 20
15 7
fields.input_format:
First line: n (number of elements)
Second line: n space-separated integers (-1 = null)
fields.output_format: Level order traversal, each level on a new line

fields.title: Longest Increasing Subsequence
fields.description:
Given an array of N integers, find the length of the Longest Strictly Increasing Subsequence (LIS).

A subsequence is strictly increasing if each element is greater than the previous one.
fields.input_format:
First line: N.
Second line: N space-separated integers.
fields.output_format: Print the length of the LIS.
fields.constraints:
1 Γëñ N Γëñ 10^5
-10^9 Γëñ A[i] Γëñ 10^9

fields.title: Min Heap Operations
fields.description:
Min Heap Operations

Implement a min heap. Process operations: insert x, extractMin, getMin.

Example

Input:
5
insert 5
insert 3
getMin
extractMin
getMin
Output:
3
3
5
fields.input_format:
First line: n
Next n lines: operations
fields.output_format: Output for getMin and extractMin on separate lines

fields.title: Valid Parentheses
fields.description:
Valid Parentheses

Given a string s containing just the characters (, ), {, }, [ and ], determine if the input string is valid.

An input string is valid if: open brackets are closed by the same type, and in the correct order.

Example

Input: ()[]{}
Output: true
fields.input_format: A single string s
fields.output_format: true or false

fields.title: Implement Stack using Queues
fields.description:
Stack using Queues

Implement a stack using only queue operations. Process a series of commands: push x, pop, top, empty.

Example

Input:
5
push 1
push 2
top
pop
empty
Output:
2
2
false
fields.input_format:
First line: n (number of operations)
Next n lines: operations
fields.output_format: Output for each top, pop, empty operation on separate lines
